      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [Director states that Forest Inspr ¶ William Ferguson. ¶  ¶ has forwarded his Report to the Lands Dept] ¶ In M to James McCulloch 15 June 1871, M complained that the 'Forest Inspector' was correspo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.07.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charles Gavan Duffy</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 5685, vol. 1871 Y, VPRS 1168/P inward correspondence registers, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; item is a register entry only, registered on 27 July 1871. See also M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>McCulloch,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>15 June 1871.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Director states that Forest Inspr<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Ferguson.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has forwarded his Report to the Lands Dept]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In M to James McCulloch 15 June 1871, M complained that the 'Forest Inspector' was corresponding directly with the government.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0355FD; ">Ferguson evidently submitted his report direct, rather than through M, to whom he was technically responsible. In W. Odgers to M, 27 July 1871 (in this edition as 71-07-21b) M was told Ferguson's report had been returned and Ferguson told 'to forward it in the regular official manner'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0355FD; ">The report was submitted to the Chief Secretary's Office on 1 August, but no covering letter from M has been found.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It was referred to the Crown Lands office on 9 July<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">1872.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #FFFF00; ">Need to check year here at PRO</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(No. 9839, vol. 1871 Y, VPRS 1168, Public Record Office, Victoria<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0355FD; ">). Ferguson appears to have questioned the necessity of corresponding through M, for</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In July 1871,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0355FD; ">he wrote</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the Chief Secretary: 'with refce to mode of transmission of his Report' (No. 9734, vol. 1871 Z, VPRS 1168, Public Record Office, Victoria).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">original<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">note raise</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">d</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a few questions. A possible interpretation<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">was</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that F sought guidance on whether he could submit report direct or must he do it through M, and was told he could submit it direct. Given the reprimands that F received for bypassing M, this would seem unlikely. So checked; the report was submitted through M, see 71-07-27b.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have amended the note accordingly.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have interpreted the letter from F to the CS as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">after</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he had been told to submit <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>through official channels, as this seems a better reconstruction, but I could easily be wrong. Is there any more clarity in the PRO CS files?</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">1872</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This must be correct, a report received inb august 1871 could nit have referred onwards in July 71.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
